The paper deals with the validation of autonomous vehicle systems using simulation-driven methods, which involves reinforcement learning and Markov decision processes. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Robotics (cs.RO) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper addresses issues related to the search procedure and the discovery of failure scenarios, which are relevant to Software Engineering (cs.SE) and Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-categories. Finally, the paper proposes a modification to the reward function, which is a common technique in Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
